reviewText:
Professionally filmed and narrated, this 60-minute video provides an excellent overview of Sicily. Combined with a good guidebook, it will be especially useful for travelers planning a trip to the (very large) island.

Among the areas visited are:

  * Palermo;
  * Mondello;
  * Monreale;
  * Citta del Mare;
  * Segesta;
  * Erice;
  * Selinunto;
  * Cefalu;
  * Ragusa;
  * Siracusa;
  * Catania;
  * Mount Etna;
  * Taormina; and
  * Messina

The video is information-dense; it provides a lot of bang for the buck. It focuses on the most attractive sights on the island, and should prove useful for a visitor trying to decide which city to use as his/her base and/or sights to visit.

My only criticism of it is that orders for it are fulfilled by CreateSpace a division of Amazon, which burns disks on an as-needed basis. Unfortunately, the disk sent to me contained significant blanks and lapses. This is Amazon's on-going problem [I have encountered it before], not that of the producers of the disk [Shepherd Entertainment Cities of the World]

There is another product that competes with this one:<a data-hook="product-link-linked" class="a-link-normal" href="/A-Slice-Of-Sicily/dp/B000W4T8IE/ref=cm_cr_arp_d_rvw_txt?ie=UTF8">A Slice Of Sicily</a>&nbsp;This one is substantially better.

Recommended Guidebooks:&nbsp;<a data-hook="product-link-linked" class="a-link-normal" href="/Sicily-Eyewitness-Travel-Guides/dp/0756661218/ref=cm_cr_arp_d_rvw_txt?ie=UTF8">Sicily (Eyewitness Travel Guides)</a>&nbsp;and its smaller cousin&nbsp;<a data-hook="product-link-linked" class="a-link-normal" href="/Top-10-Sicily-Eyewitness-Top-10-Travel-Guides/dp/0756645735/ref=cm_cr_arp_d_rvw_txt?ie=UTF8">Top 10 Sicily (Eyewitness Top 10 Travel Guides)</a>. For those interested in a more academic guide:&nbsp;<a data-hook="product-link-linked" class="a-link-normal" href="/Blue-Guide-Sicily-Seventh-Edition/dp/0393328899/ref=cm_cr_arp_d_rvw_txt?ie=UTF8">Blue Guide Sicily, Seventh Edition</a>
